  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrase groups matter most for a first Hong Kong trip?",
        "zh-CN": "第一次去中国香港旅行，最该先准备哪几组短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Start with transport, dining, and hotel. That covers Octopus, MTR, airport links, check-in, and most first-day meal stops in Hong Kong.",
        "zh-CN": "建议先看交通、餐饮和酒店三组，基本就能覆盖 Octopus、MTR、机场接驳、入住办理，以及在中国香港第一天的大多数用餐场景。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Do I still need Cantonese phrases if I can use English in Hong Kong?",
        "zh-CN": "在中国香港能用英语的话，还需要准备粤语短语吗？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "A little Cantonese still helps for taxis, neighborhood shops, and faster food ordering. Short phrase cards are useful when you want to sound more direct and local without saying much.",
        "zh-CN": "还是有帮助，尤其是在出租车、社区小店和更快节奏的点餐场景里。备几张简短粤语短语卡，能让沟通更直接，也更接地气。"
      }
    }
  ]
}
